        <page n="02" image="va.au.vv.1868.11.18.02" exists="no">
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Spirit of the Press</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Collection of news clippings responding to Grant's election. Most encourage
                    Democrats to keep working, and advise a "wait-and-see" approach toward Grant and
                    his policies.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
        <page n="03" image="va.au.vv.1868.11.18.03" exists="no">
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Lawyers</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper reports that there are twice as many lawyers in Staunton than any
                    other professionals.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Loss By Fire</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The Mossy Creek Academy and the home of its principal were destroyed in a
                    fire.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Valley Railroad</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Sheffey</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Judge</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Judge Sheffey expresses the opinion that building the Valley Railroad will
                    bring to the county an expenditure of more than one million dollars.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Personal</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Walker</ln>
                        <fn>James A.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Gen.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Gen. James A. Walker "who always led the 'Stonewall Brigade' to victory" is
                    in Staunton to attend Circuit Court.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>Staunton</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper reports that the population of Staunton has increased from 4,000
                    to 7,000 since 1860.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Clarke</ln>
                        <fn>J. L.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Rev.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The Rev. J. L. Clarke is leading a revival at Staunton's M. E. Church that
                    has been going on for the past two weeks.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>02</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The paper complains that a number of "overgrown boys" between the ages of
                    18 and 25 were seen playing mumble-meg on the lawn in front of the Catholic
                    Church while services were in progress. "Such little boys should tie themselves
                    awhile longer to their mamma's apron-strings--at least until they shall have
                    learned to deport themselves in conformity with the spirit and teaching of a
                    gentleman."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
